scheme represents blocking of the calcium channel by
binding of a calcium ion at the inner face of the channel.
It could correspond to (a) a true bimolecular binding
kinetics resulting in a bound state that blocks the channel
or (b) the net effect of rapidly equilibrating, nonsaturat-
ing binding of calcium to the channel, followed by a slow
conformational change to the blocked state. In the latter
case k+ = kf/Kdi,, where kf is the rate constant for the
conformation change, and Kdi, is the dissociation con-

