voltage is stepped from the holding potential, Vh, to a
series of prepulse potentials, Vp, for a time tp. The voltage
is then stepped back down to Vh for a gap-time tg, and
finally stepped up to a test potential, Vt as shown in Fig. 3.
The inactivation function, h, is defined as the ratio of the
peak calcium current attained during the second pulse to
Vt after a prepulse of duration tp to that attained in the
absence of a prepulse. Equivalently,

